<li><a href="/wiki/Polybus_of_Sicyon" title="Polybus of Sicyon">Polybus of Sicyon</a>, a king of Sicyon and son of Hermes</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Polybus_of_Thebes" title="Polybus of Thebes">Polybus of Thebes</a>, a king of Thebes</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Polynices" title="Polynices">Polynices</a>, a king of Thebes and son of Oedipus; he and his brother Eteocles killed each other</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Priam" title="Priam">Priam</a>, king of Troy during the Trojan War</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Proetus" title="Proetus">Proetus</a>, a king of Argos and Tiryns</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Pylades" title="Pylades">Pylades</a>, a king of Phocis and friend of Orestes</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Rhadamanthys" class="mw-redirect" title="Rhadamanthys">Rhadamanthys</a>, a king of Crete; after his death, he became a judge of the dead in the Underworld</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Rhesus_of_Thrace" title="Rhesus of Thrace">Rhesus</a>, a king of Thrace who sided with Troy in the Trojan War</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Sarpedon_(Trojan_War_hero)" title="Sarpedon (Trojan War hero)">Sarpedon</a>, a king of Lycia and son of Zeus who fought on the side of the Greeks during the Trojan War</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Sisyphus" title="Sisyphus">Sisyphus</a>, a king of Thessaly who attempted to cheat death and was sentenced to an eternity of rolling a boulder up a hill, only to watch it roll back down</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Sithon_(mythology)" title="Sithon (mythology)">Sithon</a>, a king of Thrace</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Talaus" title="Talaus">Talaus</a>, a king of Argos who sailed with the Argonauts</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Tegyrios" title="Tegyrios">Tegyrios</a>, a king of Thrace</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Telamon" title="Telamon">Telamon</a>, a king of Salamis and father of Ajax; he sailed with the Argonauts and participated in the Calydonian Boar hunt</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Telephus" title="Telephus">Telephus</a>, a king of <a href="/wiki/Mysia" title="Mysia">Mysia</a> and son of Heracles</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Temenus" title="Temenus">Temenus</a>, a king of Argos and descendant of Heracles</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Teucer" title="Teucer">Teucer</a>, founder-king of Salamis who fought alongside the Greeks in the Trojan War</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Teutamides" title="Teutamides">Teutamides</a>, a king of <a href="/wiki/Larissa" title="Larissa">Larissa</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Teuthras" title="Teuthras">Teuthras</a>, a king of Mysia</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Thersander" title="Thersander">Thersander</a>, a king of Thebes and one of the Epigoni</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Theseus" title="Theseus">Theseus</a>, a king of Athens and slayer of the <a href="/wiki/Minotaur" title="Minotaur">Minotaur</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Thyestes" title="Thyestes">Thyestes</a>, a king of Mycenae and brother of Atreus</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Tisamenus" title="Tisamenus">Tisamenus</a>, a king of Argos, Mycenae, and Sparta</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Tyndareus" title="Tyndareus">Tyndareus</a>, a king of Sparta</li></ul>
</div>
<h3><span id="Seers.2Foracles"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Seers/oracles">Seers/oracles</span></h3>
<div class="div-col columns column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em;">
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Amphilochus_(brother_of_Alcmaeon)" class="mw-redirect" title="Amphilochus (brother of Alcmaeon)">Amphilochus</a> (), a seer and brother of Alcmaeon who died in the war of the <a href="/wiki/Seven_against_Thebes" title="Seven against Thebes">Seven against Thebes</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Anius" title="Anius">Anius</a>, son of Apollo who prophesied that the Trojan War would be won in its tenth year</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Asbolus" title="Asbolus">Asbolus</a>, a seer <a href="/wiki/Centaur" title="Centaur">Centaur</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Bakis" title="Bakis">Bakis</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Branchus" title="Branchus">Branchus</a>, a seer and son of Apollo</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Calchas" title="Calchas">Calchas</a>, an Argive seer who aided the Greeks during the Trojan War</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Carnus" title="Carnus">Carnus</a>, an <a href="/wiki/Acarnania" title="Acarnania">Acarnanian</a> seer and lover of Apollo</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Carya_(daughter_of_Dion)" class="mw-redirect" title="Carya (daughter of Dion)">Carya</a>, a seer and lover of Dionysus</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Cassandra" title="Cassandra">Cassandra</a>, a princess of Troy cursed to see the future but never to be believed</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Ennomus" title="Ennomus">Ennomus</a>, a <a href="/wiki/Mysian" class="mw-redirect" title="Mysian">Mysian</a> seer, killed by Achilles during the Trojan War</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Halitherses" title="Halitherses">Halitherses</a>, an Ithacan seer who warned Penelope's suitors of Odysseus' return</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Helenus" title="Helenus">Helenus</a>, seer and twin brother of Cassandra, who later became king of Epirus</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Iamus" title="Iamus">Iamus</a>, a son of Apollo possessing the gift of prophecy, he founded the <a href="/wiki/Iamidai" title="Iamidai">Iamidai</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Idmon" title="Idmon">Idmon</a>, a seer who sailed with the Argonauts</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Manto_(mythology)" title="Manto (mythology)">Manto</a>, seer and daughter of Tiresias</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Melampus" title="Melampus">Melampus</a>, a legendary soothsayer and healer, and king of Argos</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Mopsus" title="Mopsus">Mopsus</a>, the name of two legendary seers</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Polyeidos" class="mw-redirect" title="Polyeidos">Polyeidos</a>, a Corinthian seer who saved the life of Glaucus</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Pythia" title="Pythia">Pythia</a>, the oracle of <a href="/wiki/Delphi" title="Delphi">Delphi</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Telemus" title="Telemus">Telemus</a>, a seer who foresaw that the Cyclops Polyphemus would be blinded by Odysseus</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Theoclymenus" title="Theoclymenus">Theoclymenus</a>, an Argive seer</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Tiresias" title="Tiresias">Tiresias</a>, blind prophet of Thebes</li></ul>
</div>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Amazons">Amazons</span></h3>
<div class="div-col columns column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em;">
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Bell-krater_Akhilleus_Penthesileia_MAN.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/Bell-krater_Akhilleus_Penthesileia_MAN.jpg/220px-Bell-krater_Akhilleus_Penthesileia_MAN.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="176" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/Bell-krater_Akhilleus_Penthesileia_MAN.jpg/330px-Bell-krater_Akhilleus_Penthesileia_MAN.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/Bell-krater_Akhilleus_Penthesileia_MAN.jpg/440px-Bell-krater_Akhilleus_Penthesileia_MAN.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2700" data-file-height="2160" /></a> <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Bell-krater_Akhilleus_Penthesileia_MAN.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Achilles and Penthesileia (<a href="/wiki/Lucanian_vase_painting" title="Lucanian vase painting">Lucanian red-figure</a> <a href="/wiki/Krater" title="Krater">bell-krater</a>, late 5th century BC)</div></div></div>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Aegea" title="Aegea">Aegea</a>, a queen of the Amazons</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Aella_(Amazon)" title="Aella (Amazon)">Aella</a> (), an Amazon who was killed by Heracles</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Alcibie" title="Alcibie">Alcibie</a> (), an Amazonian warrior, killed by Diomedes at Troy</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Antandre" title="Antandre">Antandre</a> (), an Amazonian warrior, killed by Achilles at Troy</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Antiope_(Amazon)" title="Antiope (Amazon)">Antiope</a> (), a daughter of Ares and sister of Hippolyta</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Areto" title="Areto">Areto</a> (), an Amazon</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Asteria_(mythology)#Amazon" title="Asteria (mythology)">Asteria</a> (), an Amazon who was killed by Heracles</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Bremusa" title="Bremusa">Bremusa</a> (), an Amazonian warrior, killed by Idomeneus at Troy</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Celaeno" title="Celaeno">Celaeno</a> (), an Amazonian warrior, killed by Heracles</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Eurypyle_(Amazon)" title="Eurypyle (Amazon)">Eurypyle</a> (), an Amazon leader who invaded Ninus and Babylonia</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Hippolyta" title="Hippolyta">Hippolyta</a> (), a queen of Amazons and daughter of Ares</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Hippothoe" title="Hippothoe">Hippothoe</a> (), an Amazonian warrior, killed by Achilles at Troy</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Iphito" title="Iphito">Iphito</a> (), an Amazon who served under Hippolyta</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Lampedo" title="Lampedo">Lampedo</a> (), an Amazon queen who ruled with her sister Marpesia</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Marpesia" title="Marpesia">Marpesia</a> (), an Amazon queen who ruled with her sister Lampedo</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Melanippe" title="Melanippe">Melanippe</a> (), a daughter of Ares and sister of Hippolyta and Antiope</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Molpadia" title="Molpadia">Molpadia</a> (), an Amazon who killed Antiope</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Myrina_(mythology)" title="Myrina (mythology)">Myrina</a> (), a queen of the Amazons</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Orithyia_(Amazon)" title="Orithyia (Amazon)">Orithyia</a> (), an Amazon queen</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Otrera" title="Otrera">Otrera</a> (), an Amazon queen, consort of Ares and mother of Hippolyta</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Pantariste" title="Pantariste">Pantariste</a> (), an Amazon who fought with Hippolyta against Heracles</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Penthesilea" title="Penthesilea">Penthesilea</a> (), an Amazon queen who fought in the Trojan War on the side of Troy</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Thalestris" title="Thalestris">Thalestris</a> (), a queen of the Amazons</li></ul>
</div>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Inmates_of_Tartarus">Inmates of Tartarus</span></h3>
<ul><li>The <a href="/wiki/Daughters_of_Danaus" class="mw-redirect" title="Daughters of Danaus">Danaides</a>, forty-nine daughters of Danaus who murdered their husbands and were condemned to an eternity of carrying water in leaky jugs</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Ixion" title="Ixion">Ixion</a>, a king of the <a href="/wiki/Lapiths" title="Lapiths">Lapiths</a> who attempted to rape Hera and was bound to a flaming wheel in Tartarus</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Sisyphus" title="Sisyphus">Sisyphus</a>, a king of Thessaly who attempted to cheat death and was sentenced to an eternity of rolling a boulder up a hill, only to watch it roll back down</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Tantalus" title="Tantalus">Tantalus</a>, a king of Anatolia who butchered his son Pelops and served him as a meal to the gods; he was punished with the torment of starvation, food and drink eternally dangling just out of reach</li></ul>
